name: concept-sheet
description:
This model is just the first dreambooth iteration for concept-sheet/old-books style. Based on SD 2.1

Installation:
As it is model based on 2.1 to make it work you need to use .yaml file with name of a model (vector-art.yaml). The yaml file is included here as well to download. Simply copy paste to the same folder as selected model file. Usually this is the models/Stable-diffusion one.

License and support:

If you like what I am doing and you want to support my current and upcoming projects: here is my coffee jar

You can use this model as you like. I love open source so have fun with it. :) If you like it I appreciate your support ^^
Cheers!

Black images issue:

2.1 models need to have a web-ui config modified - if you are getting black images - go to your config file and add to COMMANDLINE_ARGS= --no-half - potentially it could work with --xformers instead (if supported). This line might slow your generations a bit but will not affect negatively your output.



You will find example props on the images.

Embeddings:

This model works really well with various embeddings. I would recommend you especially these two:

  • https://civitai.com/models/4775/planit-a-documentation-embedding

  • https://civitai.com/models/4805/protogemb-2-for-sd-2x-768

modelVersions.name: concept-sheet-alpha
modelVersions.description:
This version is doing what is intended but is still far from what I want to achieve. You can try using the keyword concept-art to strengthen the effect.
In the future version, I would like to add more variety to a character concept. Currently, this seems overfitted. Waiting for dream booth collab fix supporting session to resume. I will be probably training on a few hundred selected images.
